Use actions, buttons, and links on records to give your users quick access to a dashboard with filters already applied.

Create custom URLs so your users can open a dashboard with relevant filters already applied.

To create a custom URL to a dashboard so it opens in a specific state, use the Share option in CRM Analytics.
Add the dashboardState parameter to the pass record ID and other filters to the dashboard. Use this syntax for the custom link URL.
https://domain.my.salesforce.com/analytics/wave/dashboard?assetId={dashboardID}&orgId={orgID}&loginHost={loginHost}&urlType=sharing&dashboardState={URL-encoded dashboard state}

In Setup, add the custom link URL to a record page in the Object Manager.
title: Accessing Dashboards from Records in CRM
